ğŸ”° ELK's architecture:
âœ”ï¸ Elastic's ELK is an open-source stack for managing and analyzing large volumes of data.  The ELK stack consists of three applications (Elasticsearch, Logstash, and Kibana ).

âœ”ï¸ Elasticsearch is a NoSQL database based on the Lucene search engine and built with RESTful APIs. It is essentially the index, store, and query application of the ELK stack.

âœ”ï¸ Logstash is the tool responsible for the collection, transformation, and transport of log file records.

âœ”ï¸ Kibana is the tool used for visualizing the Elasticsearch documents.

âœ”ï¸ Beats is an additional download that should be installed in every remote location for its logs to be shipped to the Logstash component.
